{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDczMjYxMDE1", "number": 2741, "title": "[core] Deprecate ruleviolation comparator", "bodyText": "Describe the PR\nDeprecate RuleViolationComparator. In Java 8 we can just use regular factory methods of Comparator, instead of having this class in our public API. The replacement API is a static comparator on the RuleViolation interface. It would probably make sense to make RuleViolation a Comparable for PMD 7 too. We could make the compareTo method default, delegating to the default comparator.\nRelated issues\nReady?\n\n\n Passing all unit tests\n Complete build ./mvnw clean verify passes (checked automatically by travis)\n Added (in-code) documentation (if needed)", "createdAt": "2020-08-25T14:49:52Z", "url": "https://github.com/pmd/pmd/pull/2741", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "dddbaf0a6a6ca9e2af29bdde2ee9e2979a12b752"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-09-12T10:02:50Z", "author": {"login": "oowekyala"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 5, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdCYNSRgH2gAyNDczMjYxMDE1OmZkZTIzMzMzYTBlYWE4OWMwNTQwOGFhMTczOTk4ODlkY2E0NmQ2NzA=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdIGw6SgFqTQ4NzIxODYyNA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "fde23333a0eaa89c05408aa17399889dca46d670", "author": {"user": {"login": "oowekyala", "name": "Cl\u00e9ment Fournier"}}, "url": "https://github.com/pmd/pmd/commit/fde23333a0eaa89c05408aa17399889dca46d670", "committedDate": "2020-08-25T14:37:19Z", "message": "Deprecate ruleviolation comparator"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "31b75d3acbf872dcc04964e4d5b3dafd3c0903b5", "author": {"user": {"login": "oowekyala", "name": "Cl\u00e9ment Fournier"}}, "url": "https://github.com/pmd/pmd/commit/31b75d3acbf872dcc04964e4d5b3dafd3c0903b5", "committedDate": "2020-08-25T14:48:16Z", "message": "Update release notes"}}, {"__typename": "PullReque